{{Quote|You want to know when I was really happy?"<br>"Yes, please."<br>"When I was serving my [[Soviet Union|country]], as a hero. Saving civilians in the streets, being cheered on by the crowds. Adored like a god. Невероятно.<ref>Translates from Russian to: "''Unbelievable.''"</ref> There is no higher calling.|Alexei Shostakov and [[Yelena Belova]]|Thunderbolts*}}
'''Alexei {{Conjecture|Andreovitch}} Shostakov''' (Russian: '''Алексей {{Conjecture|Андреевич}} Шостаков''') is the [[Soviet Union]]'s first official [[Super Soldier|super soldier]] known as '''Red Guardian''' (Russian: '''Красный страж''') and a founding member of the [[New Avengers]]. During his career in the [[Soviet Armed Forces]], Shostakov became an ally of General [[Dreykov]], the head of the [[Red Room]]. In [[1992]], following the dissolution of the Soviet Union, he was sent deep undercover in [[Ohio]] to infiltrate and destroy the [[Hydra]]-occupied [[North Institute]] within [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]], assigned with [[Melina Vostokoff]] to pose as an American family with two surrogate daughters, [[Natasha Romanoff]] and [[Yelena Belova]]. Upon destroying the institute in [[1995]], Shostakov returned to [[Russia]], but was eventually incarcerated by Dreykov in [[Seventh Circle Prison]] for criticizing the Russian government.

In [[2016]], when the [[Red Room]]'s activities made a resurgence, Shostakov was [[Escape from the Seventh Circle Prison|freed]] from [[Seventh Circle Prison|incarceration]] by Romanoff and Belova to locate Dreykov. Reunited with Vostokoff, Red Guardian worked with his former surrogate family to [[Termination of the Red Room|bring down]] the Red Room once and for all, putting an end to Dreykov, and worked with Belova to dissolve the remaining Red Room cells across the world. [[2027|Over a decade later]], Shostakov had moved to the [[United States]] and founded [[Red Guardian Limo Service]], but was still miserable and searching for glory. Upon reconnecting with Belova, he discovered a plot by [[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine]] to dispose of her. Learning she and de Fontaine's [[U.S. Agent|other]] [[Ghost|operatives]] have survived, Red Guardian teamed up with them and [[Winter Soldier]] to bring down de Fontaine. They went on to [[Liberation of Bob Reynolds|save]] [[Manhattan]] from [[Sentry]]'s Void, which resulted in Red Guardian, along with the other members, being inducted as New Avengers.

==Biography==
{{MD|Alexei Shostakov (Earth-199999)}}
===Early Life===
{{Expand|TB Flashback and Past Events}}
====Childhood in Soviet Russia====
{{Quote|I am ice fishing with my father. It's very cold day in this little ice shed. Cold even for [[Russia]], you know? 'Keep the vodka by the fire,' my father would say to me.|Alexei Shostakov to [[Yelena Belova]]|Black Widow (film)}}
Alexei Shostakov was born in the [[Soviet Union]] where he was raised by his [[Alexei Shostakov's Father|father]]. At one point in his childhood, his father took him ice fishing. During their trip, Shostakov lost his balance and fell into the river. Given the extreme cold that day, even for [[Russia]]n standards, Shostakov nearly lost his hands to frostbite, which was only staved off by Shostakov's father urinating on them.{{Ref|BW}}

===Russian Agent===
====Becoming a Super Soldier====
{{Quote|[[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]. My great adversary in this theater of geopolitical conflict. Not so much a nemesis. More like a contemporary, you know? Co-equal.|Alexei Shostakov to [[Natasha Romanoff]]|Black Widow (film)}}
[[File:Red Guardian in the Soviet Union.png|{{AltFloat}}|Red Guardian during his glory days]]
During the [[Cold War]], Shostakov joined the [[Soviet Armed Forces]] and was the sole recipient of their recreated [[Super Soldier Serum]]. Acting as Red Guardian, the Soviet counterpart to [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] of the [[United States of America]], Shostakov was deployed on numerous missions and soon won the acclaim of the Soviet public, gaining legions of fans and having action figures made in his likeness. During his military career, he encountered General [[Dreykov]], becoming his friend and right-hand man in the process.{{Ref|BW}}

====Undercover in America====
[[File:West Chesapeake Valley Thunderbolts.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov with the [[West Chesapeake Valley Thunderbolts]]]]
{{Quote|[[Dreykov|He]] buries me in [[Ohio]] on that stupid mission. Three years! So tedious, boring me to tears.|Alexei Shostakov|Black Widow (film)}}
Following the dissolution of the [[Soviet Union]] in [[1991|December 1991]], Shostakov found himself no longer operating in combat missions as Red Guardian, and had his uniform taken from him. In [[1992]], Shostakov was assigned by [[Dreykov]] to go undercover in the [[United States of America]] in order to infiltrate the [[North Institute]] in [[Ohio]], which was a front for [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]], which was itself deeply infiltrated by the fascist organization [[Hydra]]. Shostakov begrudgingly accepted the mission, as it was not going to be as action packed as he was used to, and was assigned to live with three people who would act as his "family;" veteran Black Widow [[Melina Vostokoff]], and [[Black Widows]] in training [[Natasha Romanoff]] and [[Yelena Belova]]. Over the years, the four became close with one another; Shostakov and Vostokoff developed genuine feelings for each other, while Romanoff and Belova formed a sisterly bond and viewed Shostakov and Vostokoff as their parents.{{Ref|BW}}

====Family Separation====
[[File:Melina & Alexei (1995).png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov tells his [[Melina Vostokoff|wife]] they have to leave]]
{{Quote|My girls are the toughest girls in the world. You're gonna take care of each other, okay? And everything, everything's gonna be fine.|Alexei Shostakov to [[Natasha Romanoff]] and [[Yelena Belova]]|Black Widow (film)}}
In [[1995]], Shostakov obtained the file that he was assigned and set the [[North Institute]] on fire. However, this put them on the radar of [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]], who were investigating [[Russia]]n sleeper agents in the [[United States of America]]. Once Shostakov arrived home, he informed [[Melina Vostokoff]] that they had to leave immediately. Vostokoff did not want to go, but Shostakov was ready to leave.
[[File:Alexei Shostakov Rifle.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov fires at the [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] vehicles]]
Shostakov and Vostokoff told [[Natasha Romanoff]] and [[Yelena Belova]] that they were going on a big adventure, and they all grabbed what they needed, with Shostakov collecting his rifle. Shostakov drove the family to a hangar, where Vostokoff boarded a small plane with the children, while Shostakov flipped over a large trailer that was blocking its path. S.H.I.E.L.D. arrived, so Shostakov shot at them to allow the plane to take off. Shostakov jumped on the plane's wing and continued to shoot at S.H.I.E.L.D. until they successfully escaped.
[[File:Black Widow 2021 Trailer 03.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov calms [[Natasha Romanoff]] down]]
The four landed in [[Cuba]], where Shostakov carried a wounded Vostokoff to a stretcher before being reunited with [[Dreykov]]. Shostakov asked to not be given any more undercover missions, expressing his desire to wear his [[Red Guardian's Uniform|suit]] and get back into the action. Shostakov gave Dreykov the file and debriefed him on the mission, but they were interrupted when Belova called out for Shostakov. Romanoff stole a gun and threatened the soldiers, so Shostakov talked her down, reassuring her that she and Belova would be fine. Shostakov then watched as the two were taken back to the [[Red Room]].{{Ref|BW}}

====Betrayed and Imprisoned====
{{Quote|Maybe I want to talk about the withering of the [[Russia|state]]. Or maybe I don't like his hair or something and I say something casually about that. Maybe, you know, I want the {{WPS|Communist Party of the Russian Federation|Party}} to feel actually like a party instead of this sourpuss organization. But instead, no. He puts me in [[Seventh Circle Prison|prison]] for the rest of my life.|Alexei Shostakov|Black Widow (film)}}
Sometime later, Shostakov and [[Dreykov]] had a falling out, resulting in Dreykov having Shostakov incarcerated in the [[Seventh Circle Prison]] in [[Russia]]. There Shostakov languished for decades into anger, self-pity, and reminiscing over his glory days, with his only solace coming from receiving fan mail from his enduring admirers and regaling his fellow prisoners with war stories, some of which with questionable authenticity.{{Ref|BW}}

===Family Reunion===
====[[Escape from the Seventh Circle Prison|Escape from Prison]]====
[[File:Ursa Major v Red Guardian.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov intentionally injures [[Ursa Major]]]]
{{Quote|Whoa, look at you, huh? All business."<br>"Trust me, this isn't pleasure."<br>"Little Natasha, all indoctrinated into the Western agenda.|Alexei Shostakov and [[Natasha Romanoff]]|Black Widow (film)}}
In [[2016]], Shostakov was arm wrestling several of his fellow prisoners while telling a fabricated story of how he faced off with and defeated [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] in the [[1980s]]. However, [[Ursa Major]] questioned the validity of his story and pointed out that Shostakov couldn't have fought Captain America since he was still frozen in ice at that time. In response, Shostakov broke Major's wrist.
[[File:Alexei gets revenge.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov gets his revenge on the guards]]
Shostakov was called to the mail room, where the guards mockingly referred to him by his old alias while eating pastries sent for him before handing him his mail. Included with the mail was an action figure of himself as Red Guardian, which caused him to reminisce. The figure's head popped off, revealing an ear-com, so Shostakov put it in and heard the voice of [[Natasha Romanoff]] instructing him how to escape. However, Shostakov could not resist and got his revenge by attacking the guards.
[[File:Black Widow (film) 22.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov makes his way out of the prison]]
As Shostakov made his way out of the prison, the alarms were set off due to Shostakov's actions, forcing him to fight his way through some more guards before knocked down the door and got outside. A prison riot broke out, and swarms of prisoners emerged around Shostakov, so Romanoff directed him to safety.{{Ref|BW}} Shostakov was electrocuted while trying to escape over the wall, causing him to fall down. Major and three other prisoners surrounded Shostakov and attacked him.{{Ref|BWDS}}
[[File:Alexei-.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov witnesses the avalanche]]
Shostakov managed to get away from them, and witnessed Romanoff land in the prison yard to assist him by taking out some of the guards. Romanoff told Shostakov to make his way through the riot. When an avalanche was caused, Shostakov rushed to higher ground to be picked up from, but saw the helicopter flying away and thought he was being left behind. Romanoff, hanging off of the helicopter, swung by Shostakov and he grabbed onto her hand, and they successfully escaped from the prison just as the avalanche buried it.
[[File:Got This Black Widow 02.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov is reunited with his daughters]]
The two climbed up inside the helicopter, which was being piloted by [[Yelena Belova]], who immediately struck Shostakov in the nose. Shostakov was confused by the aggression and asked if Belova was on her period, so she responded by explaining how that was impossible due to the [[Red Room]] giving them involuntary hysterectomy, which Shostakov found gross to hear. Shostakov expressed his appreciation for Romanoff and Belova breaking him out, but Romanoff made it clear they needed him for information.
[[File:Alexei talks about Melina.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov says to visit [[Melina Vostokoff]]]]
Shostakov revealed that he had no idea where the Red Room was located, which annoyed Romanoff, who knew Shostakov was close with [[Dreykov]]. Shostakov lamented over how he loathed the undercover mission in [[Ohio]], and then not understanding why Dreykov put him in prison for the rest of his life. Shostakov suggested that they visit [[Melina Vostokoff]] in [[Saint Petersburg]] for information. Belova stated they were low on fuel, but Shostakov insisted they would make it, only for them to crash on the way.{{Ref|BW}}

====Visiting Melina Vostokoff====
[[File:Alexei proud.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov hugs his daughters]]
{{Quote|You don't care. The only thing you care about are your stupid glory days as the Crimson Dynamo, and no one wants to hear about it."<br>"It's the Red Guardian.|[[Yelena Belova]] and Alexei Shostakov|Black Widow (film)}}
The three survived the crash and continued on foot. Shostakov asked [[Natasha Romanoff]] if [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] ever mentioned him, which annoyed Romanoff. Shostakov sensed the tension and asked what he did wrong, claiming that he only ever loved Romanoff and [[Yelena Belova]], and wanted them to succeed. Shostakov praised Romanoff and Belova for their accomplishments as assassins before hugging them both, but they pushed him off.
[[File:Red Guardian (Black Widow).png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov wears his Red Guardian [[Red Guardian's Uniform|costume]]]]
They eventually arrived at their [[Melina Vostokoff's Homestead|destination]], where they were reunited with [[Melina Vostokoff]], who Shostakov familiarly greeted. Vostokoff invited them inside her home, and Shostakov found his [[Red Guardian's Uniform|costume]], so he put it on in the bathroom, although he struggled to do so, having gained considerable weight during his time in prison. Shostakov presented himself to his family, with only Vostokoff giving him approval.
[[File:Red Guardian & Natasha Romanoff.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov discusses their time as a family]]
Shostakov joined the rest of the family at the table and commented on how their family was back together again. Vostokoff did not feel that was accurate, so Shostakov referred to it as a reunion. Shostakov then began flirting with Vostokoff, who commented on him getting fat, but stating that he still looked good. Romanoff attempted to discuss her mission of stopping [[Dreykov]], but they ended up arguing about their family, which Romanoff stated was not real, although Shostakov and Vostokoff felt they did good as parents.
[[File:Red Guardian and Yelena Belova.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov tries to comfort [[Yelena Belova]]]]
Belova was upset over her family not being real, and stormed away from the table. Shostakov decided to check on Belova, so he followed her into the other room and sat beside her, as she did not want to talk. Shostakov decided to tell a story about his father, but Belova stopped him, explaining that he had only ever complained about their undercover mission and just wanted to recount his glory days, calling him Crimson Dynamo. Shostakov absentmindedly corrected Belova, and she told him to leave.
[[File:Red Guardian (BW).png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov is hit with multiple tranquilizers]]
Shostakov got up to exit the room, but stopped himself and began singing {{WPS|American Pie (song)|America Pie}}, remembering that it was Belova's favorite song from her childhood. This gesture touched Belova, and the two of them reconciled as they sang the song together. The [[Red Room]] arrived outside, so Shostakov put on his helmet and prepared to fight. Shostakov was hit with a tranquilizer dart, which he confidently pulled out, but was then hit was several more and was quickly knocked out.{{Ref|BW}}

====Showdown at the Red Room====
[[File:Red Guardian Black Widow.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov wakes up inside of the aircraft]]
{{Quote|There's nothing for me to do. I want to... I want to break something."<br>"Oh, you do? Oh, [[Taskmaster|there]] is something you can break.|Red Guardian and [[Melina Vostokoff]]|Black Widow (film)}}
Shostakov woke up on board an aircraft headed upwards, piloted by [[Black Widow|Melina Vostokoff]]. When he overheard that they were about to land, he asked Vostokoff why they were continuing to ascend, but then noticed that the [[Red Room]] was a [[Red Room Academy|floating fortress]]. Shostakov was then sedated by one of [[Dreykov]]'s henchmen and lost consciousness again.
[[File:Red Guardian Red Room.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov apologizes to [[Natasha Romanoff]]]]
Shostakov woke up in a cell next to [[Melina Vostokoff|Natasha Romanoff]] and after collecting himself, proceeded to apologize for his mistakes as a father to her. Shostakov reflected on how he should have not let his family go in [[Cuba]], but his cell door opened and he discovered that Romanoff was actually Vostokoff in disguise. Vostokoff spoke to [[Yelena Belova]] through her earpiece, but when Shostakov tried again to apologize to Romanoff, Vostokoff revealed that he did not have an earpiece.
[[File:Alexei Shostakov & Melina Vostokoff.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov flirts with [[Melina Vostokoff]]]]
Vostokoff finished explaining the plan to Belova, she relayed it for Shostakov, who instead continued to flirt with Vostokoff, which she reciprocated. Not involved in the plan, Shostakov expressed his desire to use his physical ability, so Vostokoff directed him towards [[Taskmaster]], who entered the room. Shostakov donned his helmet and prepared to fight Taskmaster, but noticed that Vostokoff had left before he could say his goodbye to her.
[[File:Taskmaster beat Red Guardian.png|{{AltFloat}}|Red Guardian fights against [[Taskmaster]]]]
Red Guardian and Taskmaster charged at each other, with Red Guardian knocking Taskmaster's [[Taskmaster's Shield|shield]] away, and they proceeded to brawl. Taskmaster was much faster than Red Guardian, making her able to overpower him quickly in their fight. Taskmaster kicked Red Guardian down and reclaimed her shield, which she used to repeatedly beat Red Guardian. Taskmaster went to finish Red Guardian, but he was saved by Vostokoff, who threw Taskmaster into a cell, which Red Guardian locked.
[[File:Alexei Shostakov (Black Widow).png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov escapes the [[Red Room Academy]]]]
Vostokoff informed Red Guardian that they had to evacuate the facility, as it was crashing down, so they made their escape, with Red Guardian claiming Taskmaster's shield. They reached an aircraft, but were unable to find Romanoff or Belova. They were forced to take off, but as they flew back to the base, a henchman landed on their windshield, so Red Guardian threw the shield, knocking them off. However, the henchman crashed into the tail, causing the aircraft to plummet towards the ground.{{Ref|BW}}

====Family Split Apart====
[[File:Melina Vostokoff and Red Guardian.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov and [[Natasha Romanoff]] reconcile]]
{{Quote|We fight. We fight with you."<br>"I'll hold them off."<br>"Natasha, we fight.|Red Guardian and [[Black Widow]]|Black Widow (film)}}
Upon crashing, Shostakov checked on [[Melina Vostokoff]], who revealed that her left leg was broken. The two then shared a kiss before exiting the aircraft.{{Ref|BWDS}} Shostakov supported Vostokoff as they regrouped with [[Natasha Romanoff]] and [[Yelena Belova]]. Romanoff asked if Shostakov wanted to say something, but he decided not to, knowing he would mess it up, and the two held hands to reconcile. They spotted [[Thaddeus Ross]] arriving, so Romanoff told them all to leave, although they declared that they wanted to stay and fight. Romanoff persuaded them to go, and they left with the liberated [[Black Widows]] in their aircraft.{{Ref|BW}}

===Search for Glory===
{{Rewrite}}
====Living in America====
Shostakov eventually moved to the [[United States]], where he got a [[Alexei Shostakov's House|house]] on the border of [[Washington, D.C.]] and [[Baltimore]]. He founded [[Red Guardian Limo Service]],{{Ref|TB}} offering rides for business trips, school pick-ups, and funerals. He filmed a commercial with [[Dennis Lisbon]], offering a selfie with himself as Red Guardian with every ride.<ref>[[:File:Marvel Studios’ Thunderbolts* - Red Guardian Limo Service - In Theaters May 2|Red Guardian Limo Service Commercial]]</ref> However, he did lose the weight he gained while he was in prison but remained unsatisfied with his life, wanting to be more connected with [[Yelena Belova]] and work with her for [[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine]].{{Ref|TB}}

====Yelena Belova's Visit====
[[File:Thunderbolts* Trailer 6.png|{{AltFloat}}|Alexei Shostakov welcomes [[Yelena Belova]] into his [[Alexei Shostakov's House|home]]]]
{{Quote|Why do you have this photo out? [[West Chesapeake Valley Thunderbolts|We]] were so bad."<br>"You were happy. I'll make you something. You know, I'm still super soldier in his prime. Maybe you could put in a good word with [[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine|Valentina]] for me, huh?|[[Yelena Belova]] and Alexei Shostakov|Thunderbolts*}}
At home rewatching old footage of his appearance at [[Russia]]'s Labour Day parade as the Red Guardian, Shostakov heard a knock at the door. Expecting his {{WPS|DoorDash}} order, he was instead greeted by [[Yelena Belova]]. He invited her in, and as they caught up on the past year, Shostakov learned that Belova was considering stepping away from her role as [[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine]]'s operative under [[O.X.E.]] Although he had earlier emphasized how fulfilled he felt, Shostakov still praised the opportunity to work for de Fontaine.

Noticing a melancholy in Belova's demeanor, Shostakov asked about it. She admitted she no longer saw the purpose in her work. Though suggesting fame and fortune as his motivators, he also sincerely shared that his time serving his country under his moniker and the admiration he received brought him true happiness, a 'higher calling' he believed [[Natasha Romanoff]] had understood, and hoped Belova could as well. After telling her she used to be happy when Belova diverted her focus to an old photo of her [[West Chesapeake Valley Thunderbolts|pre-school soccer team]], Shostakov began preparing a meal for her and asked her to put in a good word for him with de Fontaine.{{Ref|TB}}

====[[Escape from the O.X.E. Vault|Helping the Thunderbolts]]====
[[File:Valentina's gonna burn you alive.png|{{AltFloat}}|Red Guardian arrives to assist [[Yelena Belova|Belova]], [[U.S. Agent]] and [[Ghost]]]]
{{Quote|So, I finagled to pick up [[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine|Miss de Fontaine]] at fancy event. I figure good networking, but as soon as I overhear the coordinates of the [[O.X.E. Vault|vault]], I rush home, I get the tactical beast. And then, I drive straight here.|Red Guardian to [[Yelena Belova]]|Thunderbolts*}}
While driving [[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine]] and her assistant [[Mel Gold]] in his [[Red Guardian's Limousine|limousine]], Shostakov overheard their plot to neutralize [[Yelena Belova]], who had joined forces with a few other operatives and a [[Bob Reynolds|troubled, mysterious bystander]]. [[O.X.E.]] was preparing a strike on the [[O.X.E. Vault|vault]] they were occupying. Donning his [[Red Guardian's Uniform|suit]], the Red Guardian rushed to assist them, only to arrive after Belova and the others had already escaped.
[[File:Alexei driving Thunderbolts.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Red Guardian drives [[Yelena Belova|Belova]] and her "[[Thunderbolts|team]]"]]
He offered them a lift in his limo, where he met [[U.S. Agent]], a former state-sponsored "Captain America" like himself, and [[Ghost]], whose phasing ability he inappropriately questioned. When Belova firmly stated that they were not friends, as Red Guardian had initially assumed, he instead referred to them as a team of "scrappy anti-heroes." U.S. Agent then sarcastically dubbed them the "[[Thunderbolts]]" after Belova's [[West Chesapeake Valley Thunderbolts|soccer team]]. Red Guardian was stunned that she had mentioned it to them, and the two bickered over who had actually sponsored the team.

As a fleet of O.X.E. vehicles began pursuing them, Red Guardian urged the limousine to speed up. When the vehicles gained on them, he hurled a flaming bottle of vodka at one of the trucks, but it proved ineffective. Fortunately, Congressman Bucky Barnes, whom Red Guardian recognized as the [[Winter Soldier]], intervened, quickly taking out the pursuers and forcefully bringing Red Guardian's limo to a stop as well.{{Ref|TB}}

====[[Battle at the Watchtower|Fighting Sentry]]====
[[File:Bucky with the TBolts.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov and the [[Thunderbolts]] are captured by [[Winter Soldier]]]]
{{Quote|Okay. Mr. Soldier, what is secret plan, huh?"<br>"The plan?"<br>"Yeah... I like this plan.|Red Guardian and [[Winter Soldier]]|Thunderbolts*}}
Hauled into an abandoned garage, Shostakov and the [[Thunderbolts]] were captured by the [[Winter Soldier]] to be used as evidence against [[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine]] in her impeachment trial as [[CIA]] Director. Alongside Winter Soldier, Shostakov learned that the individual accompanying the operatives, [[Bob Reynolds]], had developed superhuman abilities through a covert [[O.X.E.]] [[Project Sentry|program]] led by de Fontaine, who intended to exploit him. Skeptical of the team's motives, Winter Soldier assumed the operatives were planning retaliation, only to scoff, along with Shostakov, when they revealed they had only planned to flee.
[[File:Red Guardian laughs.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov celebrates the alliance with [[Winter Soldier]]]]
However, after [[Mel Gold]] confirmed the Thunderbolts' claims to Winter Soldier when in doubt of de Fontaine's intentions, he untied the team from their bondages and motivated them to take a stand against de Fontaine and rescue Reynolds. Shostakov loudly celebrated when the Thunderbolts agreed to help.
[[File:Alexei and Bucky discuss serum.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov and [[Winter Soldier]] approach the [[Watchtower]]]]
As they made their way to [[New York City]], [[New York]], Shostakov and Winter Soldier bonded over their similarities and their achieved [[Super Soldier Serum|super soldier serums]]. Eager to hear the plan as he put on his [[Red Guardian's Uniform|mask]], Red Guardian asked what they would do, only for Winter Soldier to respond by simply ramming the truck they occupied straight into the O.X.E. [[Watchtower]]. Accepting the simplicity of the plan, Red Guardian exited the vehicle and joined the rest of the team in fighting off O.X.E. guards, stopping only when de Fontaine summoned them to the top floor.
[[File:Red Guardian meets Valentina Allegra de Fontaine.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Red Guardian introduces himself to [[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine]]]]
When the elevator doors opened, the Thunderbolts surrounded de Fontaine, who, failing to recognize Red Guardian, dismissed him as an "old {{WPS|Santa Claus|Santa}}." She then introduced Reynolds to the team as "[[Sentry]]," a nigh-omnipotent superhero whose name Red Guardian openly admired. De Fontaine ordered Sentry to neutralize the team in front of the arriving press, branding them criminals as a means to defend herself in the trial and clear her name.
[[File:Thunderbolts D23 Brazil Special Look (32).png|{{AltFloat}}|Red Guardian states they are the West Chesapeake Valley Thunderbolts]]
Red Guardian demanded for the talking to stop, stating no one messed with the West Chesapeake Valley Thunderbolts before charging forward, much to de Fontaine's confusion. Sentry stepped forward in front of de Fontaine and punched Red Guardian, sending him flying backwards into a wall. Red Guardian struggled to get up as he then watched as Winter Soldier and [[U.S. Agent]] crashed into the wall next to him. Red Guardian then got up and charged at Sentry with his knife, despite [[Yelena Belova]]'s protests to stop.
[[File:Sentry vs. Red Guardian.png|{{AltFloat}}|Red Guardian is thrown out a window by [[Sentry]]]]
Red Guardian was quickly stopped by Sentry with his telekinesis, who held him in place mid-attack. Red Guardian swatted Sentry's hand away and began repeatedly stabbing him with his knife, though each of his strikes only damaged his blade even more. Red Guardian attempted to punch Sentry, who telekinetically threw him out of the building, momentarily suspending him in the air before pulling him back inside and into the bar piece, destroying it.
[[File:Thunderbolts Super Bowl Trailer (18).png|{{AltFloat}}|Red Guardian and the others lay defeated]]
Red Guardian eventually crawled out from behind the bar while Sentry was restraining [[Ghost]]. He attempted to strike Sentry from behind with a barstool, only for Sentry to telekinetically rip the bar out of the floor and into Red Guardian, sending him flying toward the elevator. Red Guardian laid in defeat with the others, watching as Sentry defeated Winter Soldier by removing his [[vibranium]] [[Winter Soldier's Prosthetic Arm|arm]] and slapping him with it. Knowing they were bested, Red Guardian helped U.S. Agent carry Winter Soldier into the elevator, where the team fled back downstairs.{{Ref|TB}}

====Comforting His Daughter====
[[File:Thunderbolts Super Bowl Trailer (22).png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov watches [[Yelena Belova]] storm off]]
{{Quote|You told me, 'I want to be the one everyone can rely on if they make a mistake.' That Lena is still in you. I still see her.<br>"I don't."<br>"You're stuck. You're alone. You look only at the bad. When I look at you, I don't see your mistakes. That's why we need each other.|Red Guardian and [[Yelena Belova]]|Thunderbolts*}}
Outside the [[Watchtower]], Shostakov urged the [[Thunderbolts]] to regroup, leading to an argument over whether they were truly a team. An overstressed [[Yelena Belova]] cut through their quarrel, snapping at the group and criticizing their ineptitude. As Shostakov tried to calm her, she reminded him of his prolonged absence from her life and then angrily walked away.
[[File:Thunderbolts Super Bowl Trailer (24).png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov lends [[Yelena Belova|Belova]] an ear]]
Shostakov followed, much to Belova's irritation, and was chastised once more for his irrational silence during the time she grieved [[Natasha Romanoff]]. He explained that he had assumed she didn't want to hear from him, but that he was here now, offering a listening ear.
[[File:That's why we need each other.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov comforts [[Yelena Belova|Belova]]]]
Belova opened up, revealing that she spends her days in solitude and haunted by regret, particularly over having killed a [[Anya (Red Room)|child]] her own age as part of a [[Red Room]] test. On the topic of her childhood, Shostakov reminded her of the radiant happiness she once had, and when she joined her [[West Chesapeake Valley Thunderbolts|soccer team]] as a goalkeeper to be the person others could rely on when they made mistakes. He told her he still sees that same spirit in her, that he can look past her mistakes, and concluded by saying that that is why they need each other.{{Ref|TB}}

====[[Attack on Manhattan|Stopping the Void]]====
[[File:Thunderbolts (The New Avengers).png|{{AltFloat}}|Red Guardian and the [[Thunderbolts]] rescue civilians]]
{{Quote|Bob, you hit me with that sign one more time–"<br>"I was on meth!|Red Guardian and [[Bob Reynolds]]|Thunderbolts*}}
With [[Yelena Belova]] soothed, Shostakov turned his attention to a strange, silhouetted figure hovering above the streets of [[New York City]], one that resembled [[Sentry]]. "[[Void]]," a manifestation of Reynolds' insecurities and began turning people, including helicopter pilots, into shadows, triggering mass chaos and destruction. Red Guardian sprang into action, protecting civilians from the fallout. He subsequently gave Belova a boost to help her reach a woman in the path of an out-of-control truck, saving her just in time. As the situation briefly stabilized, the rest of the [[Thunderbolts]] joined in the rescue efforts, earning applause from the surrounding citizens.
[[File:RGuardian-Worried.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov watches [[Yelena Belova]] disappear]]
Red Guardian later saved a little girl from falling debris, assuring her she was safe, only to watch in horror as she too turned into a shadow. As the Void's assault continued, the Thunderbolts led crowds into a nearby building for shelter, with Red Guardian calling for Belova to come with them. Instead, she approached the Void directly and vanished, to Shostakov's distress.
[[File:Thunderbolts Super Bowl Trailer (30).png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov fights [[Void]]]]
When [[U.S. Agent]] deduced that the Void was composed of illusions, the Thunderbolts charged into a psychic manifestation of Reynolds' [[Reynolds Residence|childhood home]], which was now attacking both Reynolds and Belova. Red Guardian and his teammates fought back against the Void as they navigated through twisted "rooms" within Reynolds' mind, each distorted to assault them.
[[File:Thunderbolts Team.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov and the [[Thunderbolts]] confront [[Void]]]]
They eventually reached a mental projection of the [[O.X.E. Kuala Lumpur Research Facility|research facility]] where [[Project Sentry]] had been conducted, only to be restrained by the Void against various surfaces while it physically confronted Reynolds. As Reynolds fought back, repeatedly striking the Void, the Thunderbolts broke free from their restraints and joined him, embracing him in a group hug. Their support prevented the Void from consuming him entirely.
[[File:Thunderbolts Walk and Talk.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov and [[Winter Soldier]] angrily approach [[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine|de Fontaine]]]]
The effects of the Void across the city faded as Reynolds calmed, though he had no memory of what had happened, much to Shostakov's surprise. Spotting [[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine]] making a phone call nearby, Shostakov began approaching her with murderous intent, accompanied by [[Winter Soldier]] urging him to settle for arresting her instead.
[[File:The New Avengers?.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov and the [[Thunderbolts]] become the "[[New Avengers]]"]]
They followed her behind what appeared to be a curtain and emerged into a press conference. To their combined shock, Shostakov and the Thunderbolts were publicly introduced as the members of the "[[New Avengers]]."{{Ref|TB}}

====Member of the New Avengers====
[[File:Alexei as an Avenger.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov promotes his [[New Avengers|team]] uniforms]]
{{Quote|I heard about [[Sam Wilson]]. He’s dumb, litigious man, but I am smart. I am smart man. I have smart solve. 'Avengerz.' Avengers with a 'Z,' there is no copyright.|Alexei Shostakov to [[Yelena Belova]] and [[Bucky Barnes]]|Thunderbolts*}}
In the 14 months of being a [[New Avengers|New Avenger]], Shostakov once attempted to persuade a woman to purchase a box of {{WPS|Wheaties}} cereal featuring the team on the packaging. He also took it upon himself to design new team uniforms, emblazoned with the phrase "New Avengerz," a deliberate spelling change in response to [[Sam Wilson]]'s copyright lawsuit against them. While he praised the texture of the outfits, comparing their softness to a baby {{WPS|Pinniped|seal}}'s bottom, [[Yelena Belova]] rejected the idea.
[[File:New Avengers look at Fantastic Four ship.png|{{AltFloat}}|Shostakov looks at a ship]]
Later, as Belova prepared the jets for launch after the [[Watchtower]]'s systems detected an [[Fantastic Four's Multiversal Ship|unidentified extra-dimensional spaceship]], Shostakov commented that they would not need jets if Reynolds would simply become [[Sentry]], to which Reynolds reminded him that he could not be Sentry again without bringing back the Void. Regardless, Shostakov fantasized about riding atop a flying Sentry through the clouds. The team then gathered to observe a satellite image of the mysterious ship, which bore a "[[Fantastic Four|4]]" insignia.{{Ref|TB}}

==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
{{Quote|[[Soviet Union]]'s first and only [[Glossary#Super Soldier|super soldier]]. I could have been more famous than [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]].|Alexei Shostakov|Black Widow (film)}}
*'''Artificially Enhanced Physiology''': Alexei Shostakov was subjected to the [[Soviet Union]]'s recreated [[Super Soldier Serum]], gaining abilities that enhanced his physical parameters to superhuman levels comparable to the likes of [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]].{{Ref|MSCEUE}} Despite his skills being worn down by his age and years in prison and further weakened by significant weight gain, Shostakov is still capable of superhuman feats. By 2027, Shostakov had loss his excess weight and appeared to be back to his peak capacity.
**'''Enhanced Strength''':  [[File:Shostakov kicks a door.png|thumb|250px|Shostakov kicks down a metal door]] Even after years of confinement, Alexei Shostakov's formidable strength remains a defining characteristic. In his prime, he could effortlessly hurl heavy metal waste vats several meters with a two-handed toss. This raw power persists, evident in his routine victories against tough prison inmates in arm wrestling matches, even to the point of fracturing the wrist of the powerfully built Ursa. Shostakov has demonstrated the ability to forcefully drag a guard through a glass window with a single arm, and he can easily knock down thick metal doors and toss aside correctional officers. His strength allowed him to confront Taskmaster without serious harm, casually swatting Taskmaster's shield with such force that it embedded itself in the floor. Despite these displays of immense power, the specialized containment cells within the Red Room Academy proved impervious to his attempts to break free.
**'''Enhanced Durability''': [[File:RGuardian-SavingGirl.png|thumb|250px|Shostakov withstands a big debris]] Shostakov exhibits remarkable durability, surviving a significant fall from the upper tiers of a gulag prison unscathed. He also demonstrates a high resistance to tranquilizers, requiring over a dozen doses to subdue him after a single shot had no effect. Remarkably, he showed no pain or reaction while being tattooed during an arm wrestling match. Despite this impressive resilience, he remains vulnerable to taser shocks and can be overcome by skilled fighters like Taskmaster. During the Battle of Manhattan, he endured the impact of a large, potentially fatal piece of cinder falling onto his back from a great height to save a child from harm, showing no signs of strain or injury, enabling Shostakov to protect her and continue moving afterward.
**'''Enhanced Speed''': [[File:Shostakov catchs the plane.png|thumb|250px|Shostakov catching up a plane]] Due to his super-soldier treatment, Shostakov can move at much faster than the average human. When he and his family were escaping Ohio, where Shostakov was able to run on foot and catch up with a rapidly accelerating plane about to take off. Shostakov also reached a child before they could be hit by falling debris.
**'''Enhanced Agility''': Shostakov is supremely agile. Even with the weight he has put on in the past two decades, he was still nimble enough to leap onto the upper levels of the gulag prison courtyard with ease, as well as jump off a guard's riot shield to gain altitude.
**'''Enhanced Stamina''': Shostakov's musculature produces far less fatigue toxins during physical activity than the musculature of an ordinary human. Despite weakened by significant weight gain, during his fight with Taskmaster, Shostakov was able to stand back up even though Taskmaster kept knocking him down, and suffered numerous hits without being knocked out.
**'''Enhanced Reflexes''': [[File:BlackWidowTeaserTrailer77.png|thumb|250px|Shostakov blocking [[Taskmaster]]'s attacks]] Shostakov possesses increased reflexes; he was able to react and dodge gunfire from police officers back in Ohio without getting hit, knocked Taskmaster's shield out of the way before it could hit him and was able to react to some of the latter's blows without worry. When he obtained a toy model of himself, the head popped off, but Shostakov caught it with perfect reaction time.
**'''Regenerative Healing Factor''': As a super-soldier, Shostakov has enhanced regenerative abilities, being able to heal bruises at astounding rates and withstand a military grade tranquilizer dart without feeling any effect or passing out before being shot with many. Unfortunately, due to his laziness and imprisonment, his metabolism has stunted, resulting in his dramatic weight gain.
**'''Longevity''': As a result of the Super Soldier Serum he was given, Shostakov’s natural lifespan was greatly extended, allowing him to live for longer than any other natural human.

===Abilities===
{{Quote|I was the muscle.|Alexei Shostakov|Black Widow (film)}}
*'''Expert Combatant''': [[File:BlackWidowTeaserTrailer79.png|thumb|250px|Red Guardian fighting against [[Taskmaster]]]] As a soldier, Shostakov is a highly skilled and formidable hand-to-hand combatant, with his role being "the muscle" in his and Melina's partnership. His skill was only further enhanced after he became a super soldier. He was easily able to defend himself from the [[Seventh Circle Prison]] guards, and outmatch multiple [[O.X.E.]] soldiers. Despite his skills, however, Shostakov was overpowered by [[Ursa Major]], though he was still recovering from a fall during his escape from prison at that time, and outclassed by [[Taskmaster]].
*'''Shield Mastery''': Given that Shostakov's action figure came with a shield, it is likely that he once used one during his exploits as Red Guardian. Regardless of whether or not he actually owned one, Shostakov was still able to use Taskmaster's shield with lethal efficiency when he killed one of Dreykov's men with it.
*'''Expert Marksman''': [[File:Alexei Shostakov shoots at S.H.I.E.L.D.png|thumb|250px|Shostakov shooting at [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]]] As a highly trained Soviet soldier, Shostakov is able to wield different types of weapons with great accuracy. During his family's escape from Ohio, he managed to shoot out the tires of multiple moving SUVs while laying on an unstable wing of a plane which was about to take off, and he is able to throw his shield with great accuracy much like [[Steve Rogers]].
*'''Expert Spy''': Shostakov is an expert spy, being able to go undercover in the [[United States of America]], and pretend to be [[Melina Vostokoff]]'s husband and the father of Natasha Romanoff and Yelena Belova perfectly for three years without arousing suspicion. In addition, Shostakov was able to infiltrate the [[North Institute]] in [[Ohio]] and successfully obtained a file that he was assigned and then destroy the [[North Institute]].
*'''Bilingualism''': Shostakov is fluent in his native Russian, as well as English. In fact, Shostakov has such mastery of the English language that he was able to perfectly mimic an American accent while undercover for three years, in public and in private.

